# Creating a list of compliance types
compliance_type = []
for i in range(len(food_inspection_data.columns)):
    if '(C)' in food_inspection_data.columns[i]:
        compliance_type.append(food_inspection_data.columns[i])
In [18]:
compliance_type.extend(['Toxic Substances & Pesticides','Rodent and Insects','Nutritional Labeling','Trans Fat Ban','No-Smoking Sign Posted'])
In [19]:
# Creating dummy variables for the types of compliances
new_dummy_columns = []
for column in compliance_type:
    food_inspection_data.loc[food_inspection_data[column].str.contains('In Compliance'), str(column)+' compliance'] = 0
    food_inspection_data.loc[food_inspection_data[column].str.contains('Out of Compliance'), str(column)+' compliance'] = 1
    new_dummy_columns.append(str(column)+' compliance')
food_inspection_data = food_inspection_data.fillna(np.nan)

In [38]:
# Creating a new Data Frame for Cross tabulation
cross_tab_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['Establishment ID', 'Number of inspections', 'Compliant After reinspection No'])
In [39]:
# Entering all the Establishment IDs into the new Data Frame
cross_tab_df['Establishment ID']= pivot_df_2.index
In [40]:
# Find the Index of NaN, that becomes the number of inspections faced by the establishment
# Find the last occurance of 0 violations, that becomes the inspection number post which the establishment was compliant
for p in range(len(pivot_df_2.index)):
    valid_index = pivot_df_2.iloc[p].last_valid_index()[1]
    cross_tab_df.iloc[p, 1]  = valid_index
    if pivot_df_2.iloc[p, valid_index-1] == 0.0:
        for q in reversed(range(valid_index)):
            if pivot_df_2.iloc[p, q] == 0.0:
                cross_tab_df.iloc[p, 2]  = q+1
            else:
                break
    else:
        cross_tab_df.iloc[p, 2]  = 'Never Compliant'

In [46]:
convert = {'Inspection Year/Month': str} 
food_viz_df = food_viz_df.astype(convert)
In [47]:
# Group by the inspection year- month
year_month_grouped = food_viz_df.groupby('Inspection Year/Month')
In [48]:
# Creating a new Data Frame to store the values needed for the line graph
line_graph_df = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Year_Month','Total Restaurants Inspected','Restaurants Out of Conpliance','Percentage of Restaurants Our of Compliance'])
In [49]:
# Storing the unique Year Months into the Data Frame
line_graph_df['Year_Month'] = food_viz_df['Inspection Year/Month'].unique()
In [50]:
# Working with the grouped data frame to get the required statistics and values
w=0
for name, group in year_month_grouped:
    total_Restaurants = year_month_grouped.get_group(name)['Establishment ID'].count()
    total_out_of_compliance = year_month_grouped.get_group(name)[year_month_grouped.get_group(name)['Is_Out_of_Compliance']=='1']['Establishment ID'].count()
    line_graph_df.iloc[w, 1] = total_Restaurants
    line_graph_df.iloc[w, 2] = total_out_of_compliance
    line_graph_df.iloc[w, 3] = (total_out_of_compliance/total_Restaurants)*100
    w += 1

Out[65]:
[]

The percentage of defaulting restaurants follows a cyclic pattern as the time goes by. The inspections find more violations after an almost equal amount of time. The lowest values are seen in April, 2019 where only ~34% of the restaurants were found non compliant. Thus, based on the vizualization, it could be said that the inspections become stricter and then easier in a cyclic pattern or the restaurants try and be more compliant at a certain time of the year always.

In [58]:
# Working with the grouped data frame to get the required statistics and values
z=0
for est_id, group in restaurant_grouped:
    total_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Number of Compliance Violations'].sum()
    total_food_approved_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Food from Approved Source (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_food_protected_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Food Protected from Contamination (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_workers_restricted_approved_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Ill Workers Restricted (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_hand_washing_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Proper Hand Washing (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_cooling_time_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Cooling Time and Temperature (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_cold_holding_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Cold Holding Temperature (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_hot_holding_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Hot Holding Temperature (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_cooking_time_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Cooking Time and Temperature (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_reheating_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Reheating Time and Temperature (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_hotandcold_running_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Hot and Cold Running Water Provided (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_sewage_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Proper Sewage Disposal (C) compliance'].sum()
    total_toxic_substances_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Toxic Substances & Pesticides compliance'].sum()
    total_rodent_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Rodent and Insects compliance'].sum()
    total_nutritional_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Nutritional Labeling compliance'].sum()
    total_trans_fat_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Trans Fat Ban compliance'].sum()
    total_nosmoking_sign_violations = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['No-Smoking Sign Posted compliance'].sum()
    latitude = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Latitude'].unique()
    longitude = restaurant_grouped.get_group(est_id)['Longitude'].unique()
    
    map_df.iloc[z, 1] = latitude
    map_df.iloc[z, 2] = longitude
    map_df.iloc[z, 3] = total_food_approved_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 4] = total_food_protected_violations 
    map_df.iloc[z, 5] = total_workers_restricted_approved_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 6] = total_hand_washing_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 7] = total_cooling_time_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 8] = total_cold_holding_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 9] = total_hot_holding_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 10] = total_cooking_time_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 11] = total_reheating_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 12] = total_hotandcold_running_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 13] = total_sewage_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 14] = total_toxic_substances_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 15] = total_rodent_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 16] = total_nutritional_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 17] = total_trans_fat_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 18] = total_nosmoking_sign_violations
    map_df.iloc[z, 19] = total_violations
    z += 1

In [93]:
# Plotting a Map using plotly to show the compliant and non complaint restaurants
class_map_data1 = go.Scattermapbox(
        lon = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] == 0]['longitude'],
        lat = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] == 0]['lattitude'],
        text = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] == 0]['Establishment ID'],
        hoverinfo='text',
        mode = 'markers',
        marker = dict(
                    color = 'green',
                    symbol = 'circle',
                    opacity = .5
                ),
        name = "No Violations"
)

class_map_data2 = go.Scattermapbox(
        lon = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] != 0]['longitude'],
        lat = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] != 0]['lattitude'],
        text = map_df[map_df['Total No of Compliance Violations'] != 0]['Establishment ID'] ,
        hoverinfo='text',
        mode = 'markers',
        marker = dict(
                    color = 'red',
                    symbol = 'circle',
                    opacity = .5
                ),
        name = "Has made Violations"
)

class_map_layout = go.Layout(
        title = 'Compliant and non-compliant Restaurants',
        mapbox=go.layout.Mapbox(
            accesstoken=mapbox_access_token,
            zoom=1
        )
    )

class_map = go.Figure(data=[class_map_data1,class_map_data2], layout=class_map_layout)
class_map.show()

We can see that most of the non-compliant restaurants are located in Silver Spring, Bethesda, Wheaton, Rockville, Gaithersburg and along the Rockville Pike road connecting North Bethesda and Rockville

From the first Map that shows violating and non- violating restaurants we can see that the violators are concentrated in below regions ,

  1. Silver Spring
  2. Bethesda
  3. Wheaton
  4. Rockville Pike Road
  5. Gaithersburg

From the above graphs for individual violations we are able to notice that the violations that contribute greatly to the trend observed in violating restaurants are as follows,

  1. Food Protected from Contamination
  2. Proper Hand Washing
  3. Cold Holding Temperature
  4. Hot Holding Temperatur
  5. Rodent and Insects violations
  6. Trans Fat Ban
  7. The Non-Smoking sign

We also observe that these violators are concentrated in the same areas as observed from the first map. Thus, confirming our findings from the map.
